OL,3,CBurnham pledges to 'make a difference
OL,4,Cthis year' on cost-of-living
OL,6,FBurnham has said now that this issue
OL,7,F"will be looked through at the Budget"
OL,8,Fbut warned, "it's difficult given the
OL,9,Ffinancial circumstances in which we
OL,10,Ffind ourselves".
OL,12,FWhen asked whether he would introduce
OL,13,Fa 50p top rate of tax, Burnham said it
OL,14,F"would be just premature" to say
OL,15,Fanything on that.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1784593081
OL,3,CBurnham pledges to 'make a difference
OL,4,Cthis year' on cost-of-living
OL,6,FBurnham also confirmed he would retain
OL,7,FSir Keir Starmer and Rachel Reeves'
OL,8,Ffiscal rules, and that he will not be
OL,9,F"taking risks with the economy". He
OL,10,Fclaimed that the funding for his plans
OL,11,Fwill be "set out in our Budget".
OL,13,FAnother area that Burnham is
OL,14,Fpassionate is social care and how it
OL,15,Fcan be better funded.
OL,17,FHe was highly critical of the approach
OL,18,Fof his "generation of politicians" for
OL,19,Fnot doing the difficult thing and
OL,20,Fchanging care and standards.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1784593081
OL,3,CBurnham pledges to 'make a difference
OL,4,Cthis year' on cost-of-living
OL,6,F"I'll be blunt with you. I would not
OL,7,Fwant to leave office having done what
OL,8,FWestminster has done, not just for 15
OL,9,Fyears," he said.
OL,11,F"If I look at the National Health
OL,12,FService right now, what I hear from
OL,13,Fpeople is that corridor care is
OL,14,Fbecoming the norm all year round, not
OL,15,Fjust in winter time, and the standards
OL,16,Fin relation to A&E are just not
OL,17,Fachievable in terms of the 90-plus
OL,18,Fpercent of people coming through in
OL,19,Ffour hours.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1784593081
OL,3,CBurnham pledges to 'make a difference
OL,4,Cthis year' on cost-of-living
OL,6,F"They say the biggest cause of that is
OL,7,Fbroken social care because if there's
OL,8,Fno barrier there at the front, how on
OL,9,FEarth can the hospital system cope?"
OL,11,FBurnham expressed his concerns about
OL,12,Fthe delay in discharging patients
OL,13,Fcosting the NHS "billions every year".
OL,15,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,16,Four political experts are across all
OL,17,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,18,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/7
